Instruction: With the good battery installed, disconnect the load module and control-module chain from the PSU. Using a multimeter, identify which PSU output cable is at +12 V relative to the other. Then, going module by module, measure continuity from that +12 V PSU lead through each subsequent module connection to the load-module 12 V input lead, and similarly trace the 0 V return. Verify that there is an unbroken path and that no pair of cables has been cross-connected such that polarity is reversed at any point (especially at the load module where the series diode is located).
