2026-04-16 12:12:38 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Load module input cables at final connection to series chain'] hypothesis_explanation='The last test shows that the PSU + and − rails are each continuous along the chain of control modules, but at the load module the polarity is effectively reversed: PSU (+) has a low resistive path to the load (−) lead and PSU (−) to the load (+) lead. This matches exactly the behavior of the series diode in the load module being reverse‑biased because the two unmarked load‑module input cables have been cross‑connected (plugged in with reversed polarity) to the outgoing cable pair from control module 8. With reversed polarity at the load, the diode prevents current, so the lamp and the internal load indicator both remain off even though the rest of the chain is intact. The PSU green LED branch reading near 0 V simply reflects that virtually no current is being drawn from the battery. The root cause is thus a configuration error: the two input cables of the load module are swapped at their connection to the preceding module. Repair consists of reconnecting them with the correct polarity.'
