Instruction: Systematically disconnect and visually inspect each pair of fast-connection terminals between modules, then reconnect them ensuring that for every module the same physical conductor that is on the +12 V side at the PSU remains consistently on the +12 V side through each module to the load (i.e., avoid crossing the two conductors at any junction). Essentially, re-seat the series chain paying attention to not swap the two cables at any module interface.
